article.linkText: Almonor scores 24, leads Fairleigh Dickinson over Manhattan 76-71
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Ansley Almonor had 24 points in Fairleigh Dickinson's 76-71 victory against Manhattan on Friday night. Almonor had eight rebounds for the Knights (6-5). DeVante Jamison scored 12 points while shooting 5 for 12, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc, and added eight assists and three steals. Sean Moore had 11 points and was 4 of 14 shooting (1 for 4 from 3-point range). Shaquil Bender led the Jaspers (4-5) in scoring, finishing with 21 points and eight rebounds. Briggs McClain added 14 points for Manhattan. Jaden Winston also put up 13 points, eight assists and four steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
